commitResults.messageBody:
Currently we do not have a feature to recall previous entered by users.

We should have a class to support this feature.

Let's add a CommandHistory class to facilitate storing and recalling
of previous commands typed by users. This will contain functions like
hasPreviousCommand(), hasNextCommand(), getPreviousCommand(),
getNextCommand(), addCommand().

commitResults.messageTitle: DG: Fix lack of paranthesis in addCommand

commitResults.messageBody: Edit attributes of member and event

CommandHistory class was created but not used in CCACommander, thereby
making it unnecessary. There was also a lack of functions in
CommandHistory that facilitates the feature of recalling past commands.

Specification is as follows:
Any command that is not the same as the last command stored into the
command history will be stored into commandHistoryList. Upon
pressing the up arrow, the user will be able to get the previous
command and display it in the command box. Similar with the down arrow
and the next command.

There is a special case of deletion. When the user presses the
backspace, it will reset the pointer and only allow the user to
recall the previous commands.

Let's include
* resetPointer() function that resets the pointer as the size of
  commands, this is past the last command.
* isLastCommand() function to return whether the pointer is at the last
  command.
* CaseSwitch statements in CommandBox based on keyPress
  * Up Arrow to get previous command
  * Down Arrow to get next command
  * BackSpace to resetPointer
* AddCommand when entering command into command box

commitResults.messageBody:
Currently we cannot edit the memberName and eventName of an Enrolment.

We should support this so editing name of Event or Member will edit
Enrolments.

Let’s add the memberName and eventName fields and their related methods
to EditEnrolmentDescriptor to facilitate this.

Currently equals method returns true if hours and remark attribute are
equal.

This is incorrect since EditEnrolmentCommand contains memberName
and eventName as well.

Let’s update the equals method to compare the equality of
memberName and eventName with the other memberName and
eventName respectively.

commitResults.messageBody:
The current behaviour of undo/redo command for Enrol specific command is wrong as
it outputs a cryptic looking message upon undoing/redoing the Enrol command. This
is due to EnrolCommand class using the toString method of the Attendance class to
output the message.

A new method is created for Attendance class, which is called getMemberAndEventAttendance.
This method formats the output message to be more user-friendly and less cryptic. The
EnrolCommand then calls on this method to display the more user-friendly message.

Doing so will make the output message clearer and does not expose the internal structure
of the code to the user.
